{"id":"225886707_A_randomized_algorithm_for_fixed-dimensional_linear_programming","abstract":"We give a (Las Vegas) randomized algorithm for linear programming in a fixed dimensiond for which the expected computation time is\nO(d(3 + ed )d n)O(d^{(3 + \\varepsilon _d )d} n)\n, where lim\ndO(3d2 n)O(3^{d^2 } n)\n. The method is based on a recent idea of Clarkson. Two variations on the algorithm are examined briefly.","authors":["Martin Dyer","Alan Frieze"],"meta":["May 1989Mathematical Programming 44(1):203-212","DOI:10.1007/BF01587088"],"references":["256181593_Linear_programming_in_On_3d2_time","228057769_Probability_Inequalities_for_Sums_of_Bounded_Random_Variables","225788704_Nets_and_Simplex_Range_Queries","221996154_Probability_Inequalities_For_Sums_of_Bounded_Random_Variables","221591823_Further_Applications_of_Random_Sampling_to_Computational_Geometry","220618059_On_a_Multidimensional_Search_Technique_and_Its_Application_to_the_Euclidean_One-Centre_Problem","220617901_Linear_Time_Algorithms_for_Two-_and_Three-Variable_Linear_Programs","220617278_Linear-Time_Algorithms_for_Linear_Programming_in_R","220452889_New_Applications_of_random_Sampling_in_Computational_Geometry","220452657_epsilon-Nets_and_Simplex_Range_Queries","220432481_Linear_Programming_in_Linear_Time_When_the_Dimension_Is_Fixed","220115563_Linear_Programming_in_On_3_d_2_Time","4355300_Linear-Time_Algorithm_for_Linear_Programming_in_R3_and_Related_Problems"]}